definition: to delay/to postpone/to keep putting sth off/to procrastinate/(computing) to lag

sentences.english: The garbage collection pause times are the most significant delays any threads encounter.
sentences.chinese: 垃圾收集停顿时间是任何线程遇到的最显著的延迟。

sentences.english: In addition, the number of the zenith delay parameters has effect on the tropospheric refraction.
sentences.chinese: 天顶延迟参数个数的选择对对流层折射有较大影响。

sentences.english: The task of mending the public finances could be postponed until after the election.
sentences.chinese: 对公共财政的修护可能要延迟到大选之后了。

sentences.english: The juice yield decreased with treating time postponed.
sentences.chinese: 出汁率随处理时间延迟而降低。

sentences.english: This delay is often a frustrating factor in cell-network data connections.
sentences.chinese: 延迟往往是蜂窝式网络中最令人抓狂的因素。

sentences.english: We can put it off till next week.
sentences.chinese: 我们可以延迟到本周较后的时间。

sentences.english: Reducing variability frequently incurs a drop in latency and throughput performance.
sentences.chinese: 减少易变性通常会增加延迟时间和降低吞吐量性能。

sentences.english: Due to delayed and irregular reporting these, figures should be considered provisional.
sentences.chinese: 由于延迟和不定期报告，应将这些数字视为临时数字。

sentences.english: But I believe I gained a lot by delaying my sex life.
sentences.chinese: 但我相信，正是延迟了性生活，我得到很多的收获。

sentences.english: Our measurements of latency are all two-hop timings.
sentences.chinese: 我们衡量延迟的标准是两跳计时。

sentences.english: But dozens of trains were rerouted, causing massive delays.
sentences.chinese: 但是数十辆火车改变了行进路线，造成大量延迟。

sentences.english: This sort of delayed coverage of significant events is standard practice.
sentences.chinese: 这种对重大事件延迟报道的方法是标准的做法。

sentences.english: El Nino events increase probability that occurs the delayed cool injury.
sentences.chinese: 厄尔尼诺事件会增加延迟型冷害发生的概率。

sentences.english: Another source of delays is miscommunication.
sentences.chinese: 延迟的另一个来源是错误传达。

sentences.english: Stable and great PTC website, no delay payment happen for member.
sentences.chinese: 稳定性极高的网赚，完全没有延迟付款的问题。

sentences.english: There was no immediate or delayed transplant-related toxicity.
sentences.chinese: 没有发现立即和延迟性的移植相关毒性。

definition: to push back (progress, the times etc)
ahead of schedule/sooner than planned/to bring forward (to an earlier time)
to cut short/to break off/to discontinue/to interrupt
to delay/to be held up/to miss (an opportunity)/delay/holdup
to cease/to suspend/to break off/to stop/to discontinue
gap/interval/compartment/to divide/to separate/to leave a gap of (two weeks, three meters etc)
